Sawyer SuperC uses three open projects:

1. **Colibri** by Vincenzo/JustVugg (Apache 2.0) -- The local inference engine.
   Colibri proved that a 744B MoE model can run on consumer hardware by streaming
   experts from disk. The C kernel code in c/colibri/ is derived from Colibri.
   https://github.com/JustVugg/colibri

2. **GLM-5.2** by Z.ai (open weights) -- The model itself.
   GLM-5.2 is a 744-billion-parameter Mixture-of-Experts model with 21,504
   routed experts. Its open availability makes this entire project possible.
   https://z.ai/

3. **Sawyer** by InFill Systems, LLC (Apache 2.0) -- Network routing and token economics.
   https://github.com/drc10101/sawyer-network